Constants:
==========
Multiple declarations: only first is saved, others don't exist
float = int 	 => implicit cast to float
int = float 	 => implicit cast to int
int,float = bool => value=0;


Variables:
=========
undeclared-> default type int, val 0
Arithmetic operations:
======================
------
Valid:
------
int   =  int   (+,-,*,/) int 
float =  float (+,-,*,/) float
float =  int   (+,-,*,/) float
float =  float (+,-,*,/) int
--------
invalid:
--------
types:
------
Error: Mismatch

int   (+,-,*,/) bool => type = int, value = value(int)
float (+,-,*,/) bool => type = float, value = value(float)
--------------------------
undeclared, uninitialized:
--------------------------
Error: Both must have a numberical value
assume type as the other operand and default value
---------------
default values:
--------------
int,float -> zero
bool -> false

Comparisons:
============

valid:
------
int (>,<,<=,>=) int
float (>,<,<=,>=) float

Assignment operations:
======================
valid:
------
int   = int
float = float
bool  = bool

LHS: declared, non constant
if invalid the value remains NULL

Comparison operations:
----------------------

undeclared -> "error in type"

Expressions:
------------
if undeclared or wrong type:
bool: 	   type:bool - val:false
int,float: type:float - val: 0 
